<section class="ui-section-catalog ui-section-faq">
  <div class="ui-layout-container">
    <p class="ui-text-intro">Quick answers to the most common questions about plans, billing, and report deliveries.</p>
    <div class="ui-section-faq__layout ui-layout-grid ui-layout-grid-2">
      <div>
        <h4 class="ui-component-list--item ui-section-faq--question">What is a report delivery?</h4>
        <p class="ui-section-faq--answer">A report delivery is one complete report for a single URL, sent by email at the scheduled time.
It includes the selected report type and the corresponding insights.</p>
        <p class="ui-section-faq--answer">Each delivery counts once per send, regardless of how many recipients receive it.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4 class="ui-component-list--item ui-section-faq--question">How often are reports delivered?</h4>
        <p class="ui-section-faq--answer">Depending on your plan, reports can be delivered weekly, daily, or monthly.</p>
        <p class="ui-section-faq--answer">You choose the delivery frequency for each report.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4 class="ui-component-list--item ui-section-faq--question">What is a report type?</h4>
        <p class="ui-section-faq--answer">A report type defines which data source is used and what kind of analysis is performed.
Each report type focuses on a specific area, such as performance or security.</p>
        <p class="ui-section-faq--answer">For example, a WebPageTest report analyzes loading performance, while an HTTP Observatory report focuses on security best practices.</p>
        <p class="ui-section-faq--answer">New report types are added progressively as WebPerformance Report expands its 360° view.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4 class="ui-component-list--item ui-section-faq--question">What are recipients?</h4>
        <p class="ui-section-faq--answer">Recipients are the people who automatically receive the report by email. This allows teams to share insights with stakeholders without forwarding emails or accessing dashboards.</p>
        <p class="ui-section-faq--answer">The number of recipients depends on your plan.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4 class="ui-component-list--item ui-section-faq--question">Do I need to log in to read reports?</h4>
        <p class="ui-section-faq--answer">No. Reports are delivered directly to your inbox. To view reports on the Board and access historical deliveries, login is required.</p>
        <p class="ui-section-faq--answer">Logging in is also required to manage reports, recipients, settings, and billing.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4 class="ui-component-list--item ui-section-faq--question">Can I change my plan later?</h4>
        <p class="ui-section-faq--answer">Yes. You can upgrade or downgrade your plan at any time.</p>
        <p class="ui-section-faq--answer">Changes take effect immediately and your available deliveries update automatically.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4 class="ui-component-list--item ui-section-faq--question">Do you offer yearly billing?</h4>
        <p class="ui-section-faq--answer">Yes. Yearly billing is available for Starter, Growth, Pro, and Business plans and includes a discount.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4 class="ui-component-list--item ui-section-faq--question">What does AI Insight do?</h4>
        <p class="ui-section-faq--answer">AI Insight highlights meaningful changes between report deliveries and points out the most relevant performance signals.</p>
        <p class="ui-section-faq--answer">It helps you focus on what matters instead of raw data.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="ui-section-faq--note ui-text-note"><small>Still have questions? <a href="mailto:support@webperformancereport.com">Contact us</a>.</small></p>
  </div>
</section>
